dcMetadata.abstract_tsi: Engraved by: R. Scot.; Shows unit positions and progress of siege with two tables of references identifying important positions and events.; Cartouche around table of references displays military trophies, including an early U.S. flag.; Copy 2 (ACQ: ?) is slightly smaller in vertical dimensions (64.3 cm) and is in poorer condition with some loss in York River and at Gloucester.; Copy 3 (ACQ: M-1363) is uncolored, printed facsimile from an original copy in the Sterling Memorial Library, Yale University with dimensions of 63.7 x 48.5 cm.; Copy 4 is Karpinski photostat 442 with additional manuscript notations in French from an original in the Départment de la Guerre, Paris, L.I.D. no. 174.
